      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(models): keep generated secret refs out of plaintext",
        "body": "Fixes #88562.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Persist generated env-backed SecretRef provider auth as `secretref-env:<NAME>` instead of a bare env var name.\n- Resolve that marker through `process.env` at model registry request time.\n- Treat string SecretRef markers as audit-safe while still flagging unresolved object SecretRefs and true plaintext strings.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: Per-agent `models.json` generation could persist auth-profile env `keyRef` values as bare strings such as `TENSORIX_API_KEY`, which looked like plaintext to the deep security audit and produced false-positive `PLAINTEXT_FOUND` findings. The repair now covers both newly generated env-backed markers and stale existing `models.json` files when the current provider context has the matching env SecretRef.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout at `/Users/andy/openclaw-88562`, branch `fix/models-json-secret-ref-88562`, commit `06a7e81ddcc389d155544c405129963f1916f041`.\n\nExact steps or command run after the patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/test-projects.mjs src/secrets/audit.test.ts src/agents/models-config.applies-config-env-vars.test.ts src/agents/sessions/model-registry.test.ts\npnpm check:test-types\npnpm docs:list\ngit diff --check\npnpm exec oxfmt --check docs/gateway/config-tools.md src/secrets/audit.test.ts src/secrets/audit.ts\nnode --import tsx --input-type=module <models-json-secretref-current-head-proof>\ngit log --format='%h %an <%ae> %s' upstream/main..HEAD\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\n[test] passed 2 Vitest shards in 25.98s\npnpm check:test-types: passed\npnpm docs:list: passed\ngit diff --check: passed\npnpm exec oxfmt --check docs/gateway/config-tools.md src/secrets/audit.test.ts src/secrets/audit.ts: passed\n\n{\n  \"proof_head_sha\": \"06a7e81ddcc389d155544c405129963f1916f041\",\n  \"generated_marker\": {\n    \"apiKey\": \"secretref-env:TENSORIX_API_KEY\",\n    \"equals_secretref_env_marker\": true,\n    \"equals_bare_env_var\": false,\n    \"runtime_resolved_matches_env\": true,\n    \"models_json_plaintext_finding_count\": 0\n  },\n  \"stale_existing_marker\": {\n    \"current_provider_secret_ref\": \"env:TENSORIX_API_KEY\",\n    \"existing_models_apiKey\": \"TENSORIX_API_KEY\",\n    \"audit_status\": \"clean\",\n    \"models_json_plaintext_finding_count\": 0,\n    \"models_json_findings\": []\n  },\n  \"mismatch_guardrail\": {\n    \"existing_models_apiKey\": \"OTHER_TENSORIX_API_KEY\",\n    \"models_json_plaintext_finding_count\": 1,\n    \"models_json_findings\": [\n      {\n        \"code\": \"PLAINTEXT_FOUND\",\n        \"jsonPath\": \"providers.tensorix.apiKey\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n\n06a7e81ddc Andy Ye <35905412+TurboTheTurtle@users.noreply.github.com> Fix stale models json secret ref audit markers\ne7741d176e Andy Ye <35905412+TurboTheTurtle@users.noreply.github.com> Fix models json secret ref api keys\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: A generated provider backed by an auth-profile env `keyRef` gets `apiKey: \"secretref-env:TENSORIX_API_KEY\"`, not the bare env var name. The model registry resolves that marker through `process.env.TENSORIX_API_KEY` at request time, and the security audit reports zero `PLAINTEXT_FOUND` findings for both the generated marker and a stale existing `models.json` value of `TENSORIX_API_KEY` when Tensorix is currently managed by that exact env SecretRef. A mismatched bare value, `OTHER_TENSORIX_API_KEY`, is still flagged as `PLAINTEXT_FOUND`, so arbitrary all-caps strings are not broadly whitelisted.\n\nWhat was not tested: The source-tree CLI wrapper requires built `dist/entry.(m)js`, so the proof invoked the patched generator, model registry, and security audit runtime directly from source rather than `node openclaw.mjs security audit --json`.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Maintainer can modify: enabled.\n",
